title: Elastic and inelastic scattering of 12.8 MeV deuterons by Al-27 and Si-28 nuclei.

x4freetext: Elastic and inelastic scattering of 12.8 MeV deuterons
by Al-27 and Si-28 nuclei.

x4codes.hlp: AGH University of Science and Technology, Poland
Univ. of Oxford, Oxford, United Kingdom
AGH University of Science and Technology, Poland

x4freetext: The 120 cm cyclotron was used.
The scattered deuteron were measured by
means of a broad-range magnetic spectrometer using
nuclear emulsions as detector.
For the relative measurements of cross-
sections a scintillation beam monitor measuring the
particles at fixed angles from a 0.4 mg/cm**2 gold
target placed in the beam in front of the main target
was also used.
A 1.76 mg/cm2 aluminium foil and a 2.43 mg/cm2 quartz
(SiO2) foil were used a targets.
Systematic error

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: Relative errors of the cross section
measurements consisted of statistical errors,
inaccuracies of scanning of nuclear emulsions
(estimated to be about 2 per cent) and those caused
errors in angle setting.
The uncertainty in the angular measurements
due to the errors in the angle settings and in the
beam collimation.
